    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-01-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-01-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="22"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d22">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams.</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1905.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-01-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 11, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I enclose a copy of a communication of the 8th of
                    December, addressed to the President by Kathleen M. Meany, in behalf of her
                    father, who appears <pb facs="0113" n="45" xml:id="pg_45"/> to have been
                    arrested in Liverpool, probably on the ground of alleged complicity in recent
                    political disturbances in Great Britain. I will thank you to take such steps in
                    the matter as in your judgment may seem proper.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <head ana="#head_untitled-missing-head-in-printed-volume">[Untitled]</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Liverpool,</hi>
                            </placeName>
                            <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-12-08">
                                <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 8, 1866</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Poor papa came to England to see his family,
                        and the British authorities have put him in prison, and the British press
                        accuse him of many things of which he is innocent. Some time ago they
                        accused him of having deserted his family. Papa never deserted his family;
                        he would not desert any one. He has always been most kind and loving <hi
                            rend="italic">to</hi> us all. He has no worldly sense, but his heart is
                        so merciful and forgiving that he would give his last cent, did they need
                        it, to the worst of his unprovoked enemies. Mamma is ill from grief. Wishing
                        to remove all this misery, I write to ask you in the name of our dear
                        heavenly Father to ask the British authorities to release poor papa.</p>
                    <p>Begging that you will kindly excuse this liberty, I remain, sir, with the
                        most profound respect, yours, &amp;c,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>KATHLEEN M. MEANY.</signed>
                    </closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p>President <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson.</hi>
                        </p>
                    </postscript>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
